<br>
Zuratuli and I had some long debates on the fact that the level 59 and 60 wizzy spells should not be harder to get then the 61 thru 65.  My argument was that in the old school, 60 was the end game, so it was right that the 59 and 60 spells dropped off of the end game critters.  The problem I felt was once PoP came out, the old school mobs were not hunted as much so therefore no more spells on the market.  After listening to Zuratuli's reasoning, and thinking about it, I'm ok with it.  If the Wizards all had everything handed to them, we all would be just alike.  The Wizard I feel is the most individualistic class there is.  In the sence that the name of that wizard is truely known, as either being a great wizard, a so so wizard or one that truely suks.<br>
<br>
If they give us something better, i will be first in line to get it.  I truely hope they continue to make our class the hardest class out there.  Make each and every thing we do a long fight.  It keeps our class known by name, not just another good warrior.  Its cool when a group will say <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Yes, get Gandalf, he is a great Wizard, but don't let him bring that bumbling side kick Zuratuli, he is always breaking mezzes</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
Hehe, had to throw that in Zuratuli :cheers <br>
<br>
Nope, I'm staying at level 60 for a while, to be able to max out my AA's quickly and then move on.  I'm the leader of a small guild of good friends, so I still only have about 3 of my 59 and 60 spells, but i make do.  I go on raids with others and keep my eye open for spells when doing the AE groups in OS.  The items and spells I do have, keep me productive in groups, for i wear, or use them with alot of pride knowing how hard it was to get them.<br>
<br>
If it was up to a vote, I would vote to keep it the same.  If they want to add some higher DD nukes, I would say sure, make them even harder to get then what we have now.<br>
<br>
