<br>
I would say that yes, your right, only I would put it like like this:<br>
<br>
Wizards get:<br>
Fire/Ice/Magic <br>
dd, pillars, spirals, rains.<br>
<br>
Magicians get<br>
Fire/magic<br>
dd/rains/dd + dot<br>
<br>
Enchanters get<br>
Magic <br>
dd<br>
<br>
Necromancers<br>
fire/magic/posion<br>
dd/dot<br>
<br>
And so on.<br>
<br>
The thing is, often, most people do not want wizards using thier area based spells. This is where our mana efficancy is. <br>
<br>
Ok, I just randomly picked level 29 for this example. The rain spell is Energy Storm three waves of 96 damage, that's 288 total (let's just assume they all land) for 162 mana. Inferno shock is 250 for 135, and Thunder Strike for 247 for 150. <br>
<br>
If a group pulls 3 mobs, and at least one person is attacking each mob face to face, and you use a rain spell, that's like a DD nuke to both of them for the cost of a little over one. Which means I did 288 damage to three mobs, for 162 mana, rather then 250 damage to each mob for 405 mana. <br>
<br>
So if I cast Energy Storm again, that would be 576 damage to three mobs for 314 mana, rather then 500 damage for 810 mana. Which sounds better. <br>
<br>
What has be come the &quot;norm&quot; is this: everyone attack the same mob. Kill it, move onto the next. Make sure you have an enchanter, to mezz any adds. Recently, I've been playing with some players that don't do it this way. They will split up the mobs between the melees. Once all the mobs are engaged, I can use a rain spell and hit all of them for less mana. The idea that tanks should stand there taking every hit is not the best. All it does is drain the cleric of his mana faster. People say casters slow a party down? HA! I hear more clerics saying LOM and OOM more often. When a cleric is low on mana, it's often ok to sit and rest and med. <br>
<br>
Yes, getting a group that can pull 2-4 mobs and having each person engage them close enough can be hard. But isn't what the lower levels are good for? Finding players you like and learning to work together?<br>
<br>
I've got friends now who say Lets do it your way, pull 3 and take them down with area effect spells. If your group knows how to do this, it will make things so easy. Rather then worry about pulling only one, now you can pull two, and not worry about that.<br>
<br>
So wizards aren't just about fast damage, they are about spreading damage all over the place. The problem isn't so much that wizards are broken, it's that most of the game has been wittled down to Tank, Cleric, Enchanter as the SAFEST way to do things. There are more then one way to play the game. I've been in successful groups that had no cleric. A druid, or shaman and once, just a paladin for healing. And we spent hours taking down mobs. The idea that the cleric should just be pooring his mana into the tanks is silly. First, they have to buff everyone, then we all wait while they med. Then you pull a few and the cleric is OOM. So you wait (but in this case, it's the good kind of waiting, cause it's healing mana) Then a few more pulls. Oh have to rebuff, now med, now fight, OOM. and so on. <br>
<br>
I once had an Ogre warrior tell me in Runnyeye, oh just sit through a few fights and think of it as free Xp. This was rather offensive to me. Then he said, I'll be brutelly honest, I don't care about offensive mana. IE, he liked clerics and enchanters. Cause one would heal him, and the other kept extra mobs off him while he hacked away. I told him, well, you better start caring about this casters offensive mana cause it's gonna be the mana that pulls your butt out of the fire when you over pull and save it with an evac, which I won't be able to do if you never give me a moment to med. Sure enough, he laughed, pulled 5 goblins, and even though I evaced as soon as I saw the bad pull, in the time it took to go off, down he went. Me and my other friend, the cleric, laughed at him behind his back. We also didn't group with him much anymore. <br>
<br>
So wizards, take control and teach the people you group with how to group with a wizard, and show them what you can do! Don't let Norrath push you around! We are the masters of damage!<br>
