<br>
Wizards get:<br>
Fire/Ice/Magic <br>
dd, pillars, spirals, rains.<br>
<br>
Magicians get<br>
Fire/magic<br>
dd/rains/dd + dot<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->I would say that is more accurate for pre-50, except for the DD+Dot.  We get one at level 44 which is almost never more useful than the nuke of that level.  The only real reason to use the DoT is for the 1-foot knockback component.  We also get one in the 50s which is marginally more useful than the level 44 version, but by then I would say my categorization is more accurate, again I was talking 50+.<br>
<br>
I intentionally did not include AE spells.  I wanted to make the point based on single-target nukes alone.. and rains which are often used in place of single target nukes.  But when you include AE spells the variety is even more pronounced.<br>
<br>
<br>
As far as the &quot;mana check&quot; debate...  there are a couple factors to this.  First of all, too often melees do, in fact, underestimate the importance of nuker mana.  For a basic encounter, you can measure the <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>power</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> of each group in terms of <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>dps * hitpoints</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->.<br>
<br>
Lets take an imaginary group.  <br>
<br>
The tank has 5000 hitpoints.<br>
The tank and melee combine for 150 dps.<br>
The wizard can burst for 300dps.<br>
The mob has 15000hp<br>
The mob deals 75dps against the tank.<br>
The mob power is 1,125k<br>
<br>
To figure out what the tank hp needs to be to win.. IE how much healing you need, we set up the following equation:<br>
<!--EZCODE CODE START--><pre> 
150<!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:yellow;font-size:x-small;">x</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--> = 1,125k
<!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:yellow;font-size:x-small;">x</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--> = 7500</pre><!--EZCODE CODE END--><br>
<br>
The tank needs only 2500 extra hitpoints to win, that's one complete heal.  However, you can also look to add damage.<br>
<br>
Assume no complete heals, and this time we solve for damage.<br>
<!--EZCODE CODE START--><pre> 
5000<!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:yellow;font-size:x-small;">y</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--> = 1,125k
<!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:yellow;font-size:x-small;">y</span><!--EZCODE FONT END-->=225
</pre><!--EZCODE CODE END--><br>
<br>
The wizard only needs to deal 75dps to achieve the exact same thing the cleric achieves with one 2500pt heal.  75dps is WELL within the range of our wizard here.  If you didn't read the math, basically what I am saying is that given a fairly reasonable scenario like the one above, nuker mana can be just as useful as healing mana when it comes to winning a fight.<br>
<br>
The difference is that melees see themselves being healed, and don't always percieve the mob being killed more quickly.  The main advantage of heals are that they are reliable.  Heals <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>always</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> do their job.  Also, when there is a need for a heal, having a heal there is critical, the consequence is death.  If you run out of damage, you can at least fall back on healing and know it will last.. once healing is gone you know you are at great risk of death.<br>
<br>
But..  The point remains that damage is worth a LOT in terms of winning an encounter, and a damage dealer can replace a lot of cleric mana for a given encounter.  Ignoring damage dealer mana very stupid.<br>
<br>
On the other hand, often it seems to be the case that I don't want the group adjusting itself to my mana.  Sometimes I'm content to be at 5% mana while the cleric is 50%.. I just nuked hard on a fight of my choosing, and now I want to sit back and rest while the melees do their job.  The only reason we've got the mana to keep fighting is because <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>I</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> was nuking hard 5 minutes ago, and I don't mind sitting out now.  If the melees think that I'm getting &quot;free&quot; experience during that time I'm sorry they're wrong, they are getting xp now thanks to ME.  If I hadn't been there they would either be dead or waiting on the cleric to med enough to pull again.  This isn't even getting in to nuking hard on multi-pulls in order to ease the pressure on crowd control.<br>
<br>
When a damage dealer says &quot;lom,&quot; that doesn't mean to hold pulls.  That just means make sure you know I'm low mana.  Don't pull anything more difficult than you and the cleric can handle on your own.  Without cleric mana the group becomes unstable, and I have no problem using cleric mana as the ultimate baseline.  But if you're ignoring my mana altogether then you're just stupid.  So anyway that's what I think of idiot melees who don't pay any attention to nuker mana.<br>
<br>
As for low level balance...<br>
<br>
I have a level 30 ranger twink, and I've taken some small bits of data and I hope to get more.  My initial impressions are that the situation is not as bad as some of you seem to think.  But to look at it in terms of <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>power</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->:<br>
<br>
A melee twink will be able to lower the DPS portion of a mobs power.  Perhaps even to the point where no additional healing or DPS.  When you don't need any extra healing or dps to win, the only thing to worry about is effeciency, specifically damage per mana.<br>
<br>
If a melee+healer combination can deal a certian amount more damage per mana than a nuker, then the nuker is weaker.<br>
<br>
For example, if a melee can deal 1000 damage for each 200 cleric mana, that's 2.5 damage per mana per person.  A wizard would have to get 2.5 damage per mana in order to be as effecient as the healer*.<br>
<br>
In the above example, there is a warrior and melee combining for 150dps, and a mob dealing 75dps.  Suppose we have a cleric landing complete heals at 25% of the warrior's hp, so every 4000 damage from the mob the cleric spends 400 mana on a heal.  The mob takes about 53 seconds to deal 4000 damage, and during that time the melees can expect to deal 8000 damage.<br>
<br>
8000damage/400mana/3people = 6.67 damage/mana/person<br>
<br>
For the wizard to match healing mana effeciency, for this specific, contrived scenario, the wiz would need to beat 6.67 damage per mana (unspecialized).<br>
<br>
It's quite possible that at some stages of the game, the damage/mana/person of a healer is vastly superior to the damage/mana of a nuker.<br>
<br>
One last thing:  This isn't the &quot;well melees need healers&quot; argument.  This isn't about melee vs. wizard dps it's about healer vs. wizard mana, those are related through melee dps.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="font-size:x-small;">*Also note that there is only so much healing that is useful.  Beyond a certian point there is no need for healing and the only useful mana is mana spent on damage directly.</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--> <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.showMessageRange?topicID=868.topic&start=1&stop=20>1</a><a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.showMessageRange?topicID=868.topic&start=21&stop=40>2</a> <b>3</b> <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.showMessageRange?topicID=868.topic&start=61&stop=80>4</a><a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.showMessageRange?topicID=868.topic&start=81&stop=100>5</a><a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.showMessageRange?topicID=868.topic&start=101&stop=120>6</a><a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.showMessageRange?topicID=868.topic&start=121&stop=140>7</a><a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.showMessageRange?topicID=868.topic&start=141&stop=160>8</a><a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.showMessageRange?topicID=868.topic&start=161&stop=180>9</a><a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.showMessageRange?topicID=868.topic&start=181&stop=181>10</a> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.showPrevMessage?topicID=868.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.showNextMessage?topicID=868.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br></td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.emailToFriend?topicID=868.topic><img src=http://www.ez